    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.8.0-dev-818-g0d9e09bf6\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.25.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean` with ASAN\r\n2. Source the following Lua file:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal handle, _ = vim.loop.spawn(vim.v.progpath, {\r\n  args = {'-u', 'NONE', '--headless'},\r\n}, function()\r\n  vim.schedule(function() end)\r\nend)\r\n\r\nvim.schedule(function()\r\n  handle:kill(15)\r\nend)\r\n\r\nvim.cmd('quit')\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNo memory leak\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nMemory leak:\r\n```\r\n1 lua references were leaked!\r\n=================================================================\r\n==2804382==ERROR: LeakSanitizer: detected memory leaks\r\n\r\nDirect leak of 3 byte(s) in 1 object(s) allocated from:\r\n    #0 0x562d03a50d79 in malloc (**/build/bin/nvim+0xcd1d79)\r\n    #1 0x562d04767352 in try_malloc **/src/nvim/memory.c:76:15\r\n    #2 0x562d0476751c in xmalloc **/src/nvim/memory.c:110:15\r\n    #3 0x562d045645b6 in nlua_ref **/src/nvim/lua/executor.c:1149:56\r\n    #4 0x562d04564630 in nlua_ref_global **/src/nvim/lua/executor.c:1158:10\r\n    #5 0x562d04570d30 in nlua_schedule **/src/nvim/lua/executor.c:329:15\r\n    #6 0x562d053fd0f5 in lj_BC_FUNCC (**/build/bin/nvim+0x267e0f5)\r\n\r\nSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: 3 byte(s) leaked in 1 allocation(s).\r\n```",
